# astroapi-go SDK

Pure Go HTTP client SDK for Astrology API v3. Module `github.com/astro-api/astroapi-go`. Go 1.23. Only external dep: `testify` for tests.

## Key files

- `client.go` — root `AstrologyClient`, `NewClient()` constructor
- `categories/base.go` — `BaseCategoryClient` shared HTTP logic
- `shared/shared.go` — `BirthData`, `Subject`, `DateTimeLocation`, `AstrologyOptions`, etc.
- `option/option.go` — functional options pattern
- `errors/error.go` — `AstrologyError` type

## Import aliases

```go
import astroapi "github.com/astro-api/astroapi-go"
import astroerrors "github.com/astro-api/astroapi-go/errors"
```

## Commands

- Build: `make build`
- Test: `make test`
- Lint: `make lint`
- Format: `make fmt`
- Single test: `go test -race -run TestName ./categories/<name>/`

## Versioning

Git tags following semver: `v{MAJOR}.{MINOR}.{PATCH}`

- PATCH: bug fix, docs
- MINOR: new category/method (backwards-compatible)
- MAJOR: breaking API change

Release: `git tag vX.Y.Z && git push origin vX.Y.Z`

v2+ requires module path suffix (`/v2`) and updating all internal imports.
